FY 2026 Base Plans:
The baseline capability of I-Predict (Incapacitation Prediction for Readiness in Expeditionary Domains -
an Integrated Computational Tool) will transition from the ONR/FNC performers into the lavatory and T&E
infrastructure of the Human Systems Engineering Department (HSED). The first use cases will complete
verification and validation of the modeling capability. The biofidelic models will aid with design, development,
and testing of advanced personal protective equipment (PPE - e.g., crashworthy seating, vibration mitigation,
helmet mounted displays, night vision devices, oxygen masks, etc.). The HSED lab will work with acquisition
community to incorporate this biomedically based model to enable improved risk assessment and testing to
allow informed trade-offs. From these meetings, the model will continue to be advanced, matured and spirally
developed. This will be accomplished by using I-Predict's research, performers, testing results and cadaver
based digital twins to improve the bio fidelity of the model. Expansion of the digital human modeling capability
will be used to assess head, neck, spine vertebral alignment/position for the design of PPE and seating systems.

