upgrade type approach, the algorithms, subsystems/sensor components, monitors and warning systems will
continue to be refined and improved and transitioned. Verify and validate performance and refine component
and subsystem capability as required. Managing the data is also another key aspect of this effort. In addition,
human performance, leading edge human interfaces and physiology will be advanced as these sub-systems
converge into systems for future Naval aircrew.

Advance Aircrew Systems for current/future missions while addressing Aircrew Endurance. Advancements
will address obsolete and out-of-date aircrew systems that no longer meet and/or address current fleet needs/
requirements. Areas include: back and neck pain/injury; reducing bulk and weight of aircrew systems; acute and
chronic injury mechanisms; aircrew protection and performance; potential longer recovery times in water; polar
missions; and pre-conditioning.
