Title: Primary Dosimetry                                                                                               0.218   0.083          0.034   0.000   0.034
                                                                                                          Articles:       -       -              -       -        -
Description: The need for primary dosimetry is inherent due to the Navy's operation of nuclear reactors and
their emission of ionizing radiation. Title 10 CFR 20.1502 states "Each licensee shall monitor exposures
to radiation and radioactive material at levels sufficient to demonstrate compliance with the occupational
dose limits." A primary dosimeter must pass accreditation proficiency testing, allowing the reading obtained


