FY 2025 Plans:
- Continue transition of Torpedo Defense (TD) Doppler Matched Active Processing (DMAP) capability for towed
arrays, leveraging ASW investment.
- Investigate and develop an extension of Passive Coherent Processing (PiCP)-for-TD technology to operate for
ASW.
- Continue transition of cross-array PiCP technology into the AN/SQQ-89A(V)15 Surface Ship ASW Combat
System production program for TD.
- Investigate and test extending DMAP-for-ASW to use all active waveforms for ASW and TD.
- Initiate testing and integration of augmented Continuous Active Sonar (CAS) enhancements into the Pulsed
Active Sonar (PAS) and CAS baselines for the AN/SQQ-89A(V)15 Surface Ship ASW Combat System.
- Continue efforts to develop and test Joint Passive Active Localization (JPAL) for TD and ASW.
- Initiate development and testing of Operator Machine Interface (OMI) enhancements to display cross-array
PiCP acoustic/automation data.
- Investigate use of modern classifier techniques for CAS.
- Awarded new Broad Agency Announcement (BAA) development contract in support of AN/SQQ-89A(V)15
Surface Ship ASW Combat System Fleet requirements.
