generators) and ship electrical distribution systems. The EM is a common, modular, scalable intermediate power
system that standardizes energy storage across multiple mission systems (lasers, advanced radars, Surface
Electronic Warfare Improvement Program (SEWIP), and other pulsed loads) and ships classes, and eliminates
wasteful need for mission systems to each develop, build, test, qualify/certify and support their own unique
energy storage systems. The EM also provides stable backup power functionality and leads to reduction of
uninterruptable power supplies (UPS) aboard ship and provides a means for recovery from ship-wide power
loss. Energy Magazine is designed for both new construction and back-fit applications where advanced combat
systems are being deployed.

Energy Magazine (EM): Continued detail design, completed engineering development models of power
converters for de-risk testing, completed input power string de-risk testing and began battery power converter
testing in preparation of the Critical Design Review. Begin procurement of all remaining material to fabricate
and assemble EM first unit and begin fabrication of first article. Update EM models and conduct component
and system simulations that focus on EM software development and EM performance in preparation of Critical
Design Review. Generate and validate detailed interface requirements, test plans and procedures for use in
virtual environment demonstration(s) and independent government testing to confirm performance requirements.
