convert ship's power for use by a future high powered ships' equipment with different voltage requirements,
such as radars, sensors, etc. Utilize Silicon Carbon (and other high bandgap semiconductor materials) power
electronic modules that enable more compact, thermally tolerant power conversion equipment making them
highly desirable for naval applications.

