A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
As a minimally-manned ship, the LCS uses a Train-to-Qualify (T2Q)/TYCOM Certification Training process in an off-ship/shore-based virtual ship trainer environment.
These simulators and blended training solutions focus on tactical, equipment operations, and maintenance training. When completely developed and procured, the LCS
shore-based training capability will satisfy individual, team, unit, and force training, with an objective of meeting Capability Development Document (CDD) T2Q/TYCOM
Certification Training Key Performance Parameter (KPP) requirements.

 Funding will develop upgrades of the Surface Training Advanced Virtual Environment (STAVE) courseware and associated simulators to achieve the training objectives.
 Additionally, after fielding more of the systems and courseware, out-year funding will be utilized to upgrade training to maintain conformity with LCS configurations and
 approved operational technical manuals and procedures, as well as test and evaluate training devices to verify compliance with requirements.

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions, Article Quantities in Each)                                                              FY 2026 FY 2026 FY 2026
                                                                                                                      FY 2024 FY 2025         Base    OOC     Total
Title: LCS Total System Training Architecture                                                                            0.901   0.934          0.000   0.000   0.000
                                                                                                            Articles:       -       -              -       -        -
FY 2025 Plans:
FY25 RDTE funding supports government labor and oversight to complete the Engineering Plant Technician
course for the Freedom Variant LCS. The course is being developed under Surface Training Advanced Virtual
Environment (STAVE)- LCS and utilizes virtual immersive training to meet train to qualify (T2Q) and Type
Commander Certifications and training requirements for this Engineering watch station. The course is planned
for Fleet delivery late in FY25.
The FY25 effort also aims to update the existing Combat Systems training courseware for Independence and
Freedom variant ships by conducting an analysis to determine alternative media solutions that are Surface
Training Advanced Virtual Environment (STAVE) compliant and provide an improved, blended training solution.
This will take into account the updated systems coming to the LCS Class like Lethality and Survivability
modifications. The recommendations produced from the analysis aim to reduce the associated funding
requirements while increasing speed to the Fleet.
