FY 2025 Plans:
FY 2025 Plans:
Execute live-fire tests required in support of generating empirical LFT&E survivability data to continue the
verification, validation, and accreditation of multiple LFT&E survivability models. Conduct networked, multi-site
land based Early Integration Testing events to include post-analysis and correction. Mature Test Procedures
submitted for Government Furnished Equipment (GFE), review and finalize test plans suitable for shipyard stage
testing aligned to the Integrated Master Schedule. Develop test data repository, review and assess historical
test results applicable to FFG for DT and OT data to reduce future at-sea testing requirements. Conduct review
and analysis required to incorporate integrated Warfare System baseline test requirements to inform Combat
System Test Bed (CSTB) development, verification, validation, and initial test runs. Utilize Early Operational
Assessment (EOA) results for iterative assessment of the following: draft CONOPS, preliminary ship design
documentation, planned mission critical systems hardware and software versions and how they are to be
integrated into the ship design, and manning and training plans. Conduct Cyber Risk Assessment and Cyber
Table Top Exercise to evaluate the platform cyber security and HM&E Enclave to identify vulnerabilities and
develop recommended actions for improving cyber readiness and posture for the program. Develop FFG LBES
design and continue coordination with NAVFAC and NSWC Philadelphia to execute construction efforts to meet
program test objectives. Develop test indices and sequences to support future component, system, and plant
light-offs. Conduct assessments, analysis, and coordination required with key test stakeholders to update test
events for SUW, ASW, AAW and Cyber in the FFG 62 Test and Evaluation Master Plan.

