       FY24 budget decrease of $15.391M due to $2.469M Small Business Innovation Research (SBIR) execution realignment, and Congressional Adjustments of
       $10.112M for "Unjustified Growth in Warfare Systems Development", $2.8M for "Live Fire Test and Evaluation early to need" and $1K for "Misc Adjustments".

       FY25 budget decreased of $2.176 due to "Test and Evaluation early to need".

       FY26 budget decrease of $23.702 due to $17.448 rephasing of FFG 62 Test and Evaluation funding based on construction delays, $433K NWCF Rate
       Adjustments, $433K Rephasing Realignment and $5.388M Congressional adjustments.

