A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The Family of Anti-Armor Weapon Systems (FOAAWS) portfolio supports the Shoulder-launched Multipurpose Assault Weapon (SMAW) Follow-On solution. The
solution is the Multi-purpose Anti-Armor Weapon System (MAAWS) M3A1, which is a portable, shoulder-fired, line-of-sight, reloadable, 84mm recoilless rifle. The
MAAWS provides anti-armor, anti-personnel, anti-material, and assault capabilities to Marine Rifle Squads, Combat Engineers, and Reconnaissance Teams to
effectively execute both offensive and defensive operations. Also contained in FOAAWS is the research, development, test, and evaluation for a suite of ammunition
which supports a wide range of mission sets including obscuration, illumination, anti-personnel, armored penetration, bunker penetration, and soft target engagement.
This line also supports the development of training aids and materiels to include reduced impacts of blast over pressure and impulse noise on the Fleet Marine Force
(FMF).

