FY 2026 Base Plans:
FY2026 will continue efforts to facilitate the transition of initial Rapid Large Area Clearance (RLAC) prototypes
identified from the Defense Innovation Accelerator (DIA) and bridge the gap toward fieldable joint material
solutions.

During this period, the Rapid Area Detection (RAD) program will have requirements validated to enter into the
Software Acquisition Pathway (SWP) and begin work to deliver an initial Minimum Viable Product (MVP) for ATR
algorithms. Standoff Render Safe and Disrupt (SRSD) work will continue in the engineering, manufacturing, and
development phase of acquisition for the SRSD portfolio while a disrupt annex continues through requirements
validation. RAD and SRSD will leverage EOD unmanned sensors and payloads S&T prototypes from the RLAC
DIA to incorporate into their portfolio.

The Timed Firing Device (TFD) will finish the engineering, manufacturing, and development phase with a
Milestone C (MS C) decision to move into production in FY26.
