Title: Hazardous Material Control and Management                                                                     1.019       1.000       1.000      0.000       1.000
                                                                                                     Articles:          -           -           -          -           -
Description: A wide variety of Hazardous Materials (HM) are used to construct, operate and maintain Navy
ships and submarines. These HMs include cleaning compounds, solvents, adhesives, sealants, corrosion
preventive compounds, acids, alkalis, oxidizers, lubricants, functional fluids, and many other products.
Hazardous Material Control and Management addresses environmental, safety, and health risks to ship
construction workers, Ship's Force, and shipyard workers.

FY 2025 Plans:
- Identify and implement alternatives to targeted chemicals in maintenance actions and parts lists
- Analyze annual procurement data to identify hazardous material (HM) trends
- Investigate high-volume excess materials and establish solutions to reduce high-volume offloads
- Characterize procurement data across a deployment to support HM lifecycle analysis
- Solicit industry for paint can crusher solution for HM offload cost avoidance method
FY 2026 Base Plans:
- Continue to assess less hazardous or non-hazardous substitutes for high-risk HM regulated under Toxic
Substance Control Act (TSCA).
- Continue identifying and implementing alternatives to known human carcinogens (KHC)
- Continue assessing procurement data to identify HM trends
- Assess emergent COTS HM management processes and pollution prevention technologies that improve
warfighter readiness at minimal life cycle cost
- Identify HM control and pollution prevention systems for detailed acquisition and evaluation
FY 2026 OOC Plans:
N/A
