 flexible digital beamforming, signal processing, signal synthesizer architecture, and smaller digital receiver-exciter systems, resulting in smaller systems for size/weight/
 power efficiencies. HPA development improves manufacturability and reduces costs.

 FY27 funding supports: SPY-6(V)1 integration with AEGIS Baseline 10, testing at Advanced Radar Development Evaluation Laboratory (ARDEL), and Virtual Test
 Environment (VTE) integration. SPY-6(V)2/3 integration with Ship Self Defense System (SSDS) Baseline 12 meeting the Battlespace Awareness Interface Control
 Document (ICD) requirements, including Land Based Test Site testing and SYY-1 Air Traffic Control System and Cooperative Engagement Capability (CEC) integration.
 SPY-6(V)4 continues testing at ARDEL/Combat System Engineering Development Site (CSEDS), requirements updates, and defect correction. SPY-6 enhancements
 include second-source RF Head testing, HPA testing, and M&S support. Commence R&D transition of ASPIRE, ROCR, Radar Advanced Signal Processing (RASP),
 EMPIRE Future Naval Capabilities (FNC) Technology Deployment Agreements (TDAs) plus Subarray Transmit Orthogonality for Receive Multiplexing (STORM).
 Complete SPY-6(V)1 testing and declare Initial Operational Capability (IOC).

