D. Acquisition Strategy
The E-130J program acquisition strategy is designed to expedite the development, test, and deployment of this critical NC3 system of systems through the use of an
existing aircraft (C-130J-30) and leveraging existing mission systems technology to minimize the need for new development. The E-130J program will competitively
procure E-130J TACAMO-only NC3 aircraft (E-130J TACAMO Weapon Systems (TWS) aircraft), comprised of three Engineering Development Models (EDMs), up to
three System Demonstration Test Articles (SDTAs), and up to 6 Low Rate Initial Production (LRIP) operational aircraft (Min 3/Max 6). SDTA aircraft will be retrofitted into
a fleet configuration and provided to the fleet as deployable aircraft upon completion of Engineering, Manufacturing, and Development (EMD) testing.




