Remarks

D. Acquisition Strategy
Precision Attack Strike Munition (PASM) - A rapid prototyping Middle Tier Acquisition (MTA) Strategy pursuant to FY 2016 NDAA Section 804 is being used for an Other
Transaction Authority (OTA) prototype contract. Continued development of the platform integration solution, launcher solution, payload, vehicle prototype and System
Development Test Articles (SDTAs). The MTA pathway enables the rapid development of PASM field-able prototypes that demonstrate new capabilities, and/or rapidly
field PASM production quantities with proven technologies that require minimal development. Follow-on increments may include increased range, alternate seekers,
alternate payloads and capability upgrades.

 The Modular Common Launcher (MCL) will design, develop, prototype and test the next generation launcher that will enable carriage of PASM on the AH-1Z aircraft. In
 addition, the MCL will provide a replacement for the M299 launcher to eliminate obsolescence issues and provide a platform for future integration of current weapons
 (JAGM, Hellfire, Rockets) and future weapons (Advanced APKWS, Air Launched Effects). NAVAIR will combine MCL contracting, development, qualification, testing
 and productions efforts with the Army's Multiple Effects Launcher (MEL) program wherever possible to eliminate duplication, reduce overall program cost and accelerate
 program schedule. The MCL will incorporate required changes to the MEL Carriage System Electronics and incorporate a Weapon Adapter Assembly with eject
 capability to facilitate carriage of PASM and integration on the AH-1Z and MH-60 aircraft.




